## Django Installation:
-----------------------
(https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/1.11/topics/install/)

-> Install python

# Install Apache and mod_wsgi:
------------------------------
-> Django comes with inbuilt light weight server [not apache].

  Follow this if willing to deploy in production : check docs

# Get your database running:
----------------------------
 -> Officially supported database servers : PostgreSQL, MySQL, Oracle and SQLite.

 -> SQLite doesn’t require running a separate server.

 -> In addition to a database backend, you’ll need to make sure your Python database bindings are installed :

    Database        python package
    --------        --------------
    PostgreSQL      psycopg2
    MySQL           mysqlclient
    Oracle          cx_Oracle

  -> For django to use manage.py migrate to automatically create database, it will need required premissions.

# Remove any old versions of Django :
-------------------------------------
-> If previously used pip to install djagno then simply use pip to install latest version and it will take care of
   removing old version.


# Install the Django code:
--------------------------
  # Installing an official release with pip:
    -> Inside the virtualenv : $pip install Django

  # Installing a distribution-specific package:

  # Installing the development version:
    -> If you’d like to be able to update your Django code occasionally with the latest bug fixes and improvements,
       follow these instructions : 
       [check docs]
